dismissalComment.html: strikes first ball! An excellent match continues for Stokes. It was a back-of-a-length cutter, gripped a little on the pitch, which Maxwell tried to swing with all his power through the leg side but only got a thin edge to Buttler

dismissalComment.html: down leg side and this flicks something on the way through to Buttler. It sounded thuddy as if it was pad, and the caught-behind appeal is turned down. England want a review. Well, this is very interesting. The front-on view didn't seem to support the review but Hot Spot has shown something. A clear mark on Hot Spot from the side on camera and this is out! What a good review - the sound didn't seem like bat, but Hot Spot said it was off the face of the bat before the pad. After the umpires also double-check that the ball has carried, Bailey has been given out!

dismissalText.commentary: James Pattinson c †Buttler b Bresnan 4 (9b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 44.44

commentTextItems.html: it's over! England have won! Pattinson skies a high top edge that flies over the head of the keeper, but Buttler is good enough to run back and take a well-judged catch

commentPostTextItems.html: So there you have it - England have avoided what would have been an equal record 10th straight loss across all formats for them. It's their first win of the tour in a full international. Yes, the series is dead, and yes, Australia have rested four of their best players, but at this point England will take anything. It was a strong batting effort that set this up, through Stokes and Buttler especially. Finch's century gave the Australians hope but four wickets to Stokes and five catches to Buttler made sure of the win for England.
With that, Australia's reign at No.1 on the ODI rankings ends after two days. They drop back down to No.2 and India by default return to No.1.

Australia's stand-in captain George Bailey says Australia struggled to control the ball with so many wides and England getting away to a quick start really hurt. "I don't think we've quite nailed down our death bowling yet," Bailey said.

Man of the Match is Ben Stokes. "We batted really well and then I thought we were really consistent and put a lot of pressure on with the ball," Stokes said. "I do love the challenge in every game against Australia, the old foe."

Alastair Cook at last gets to answer some questions about a victory. Relief? "Yeah, it's been a while since we've had this feeling. It's been a frustrating tour and we've played a long way below our potential. The good thing is we know it's there ... when you see the way people have performed today you know we're not a bad side."

That's it from the WACA. What a relief for England to finally get a win on the board. It won't be a record losing streak. It won't be 10-0 or 13-0. Now the question is can they keep it up come Adelaide on Sunday? Join us then for the final match of the ODI series, until then, from Brydon Coverdale and Andrew McGlashan it's goodbye for now.

commentTextItems.html: thumps this out to deep midwicket in the air for a couple more
beaten outside off - or is it? Jams down on the ground to a wide one and Hot Spot shows a little tickle on the bat there but England didn't really appeal

another one has been skied and another one doesn't get taken in the deep! This one was a top edge that flew out towards deep square leg, the men from deep midwicket and deep fine leg converged but neither quite got there. Ballance from fine leg very nearly made it, but perhaps just misjduged it a touch

Pattinson chips this over cover for another single
bangs it in short now for an above-the-head wide

is this it? Is this the win? No! Oh dear, Stokes has dropped a chance at deep midwicket! Coulter-Nile has launched this high out into the deep and it was a pretty straightforward chance that just slipped through the fingers of Stokes.

commentPreTextItems.html: Jordan comes back now after Broad finishes his ten.

driven hard down the ground to mid-off

dismissalText.commentary: Dan Christian c Ballance b Broad 23 (19b 1x4 1x6 48m) SR: 121.05

commentTextItems.html: Christian is gone now, yet another batsman in this match caught at third man. He's swung hard and a thickish edge is taken by a sliding Gary Ballance

commentPostTextItems.html: So England are now one wicket away from their first win in a full international in this series. Yes, it's a dead rubber in the ODI series, but they'll be celebrating tonight. And so will India - an England win here will by default put them back on top of the one-day rankings.

dismissalComment.html: Morgan is gone, he has flicked a low full toss from Faulkner to midwicket where Christian takes a pretty straightforward catch.

dismissalText.commentary: Jos Buttler c Johnson b Faulkner 71 (43b 6x4 4x6 52m) SR: 165.11

dismissalComment.html: Buttler's entertaining innings comes to an end, he's swung hard outside off and this slices off the top edge and flies away towards third man where Johnson comes in and takes the catch

headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tim Bresnan c Johnson b Faulkner 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: another catch at third man! Would you believe it? Bresnan has sliced this one off the edge and Johnson makes good ground to his left to take the catch

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shaun Marsh c Bell b Bresnan 15 (17b 2x4 0x6 31m) SR: 88.23

dismissalComment.html: top catch! Marsh trying to guide this delivery down to third man, was a little close to him and the thick outside edge is grabbed by Bell diving high to his left at second slip. A good start from Bresnan is rewarded

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch c Broad b Bresnan 108 (111b 8x4 4x6 151m) SR: 97.29

dismissalComment.html: massive moment! Finch guides a short-of-a-length delivery towards third man where Broad runs around the rope and holds a well-judged catch

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Wade c Cook b Bopara 23 (42b 1x4 0x6 51m) SR: 54.76

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, Wade has tried to force the pace now with a drive over long-off but all he's managed to do was find Cook in the ring

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey c †Buttler b Stokes 11 (15b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 73.33

dismissalComment.html: down leg side and this flicks something on the way through to Buttler. It sounded thuddy as if it was pad, and the caught-behind appeal is turned down. England want a review. Well, this is very interesting. The front-on view didn't seem to support the review but Hot Spot has shown something. A clear mark on Hot Spot from the side on camera and this is out! What a good review - the sound didn't seem like bat, but Hot Spot said it was off the face of the bat before the pad. After the umpires also double-check that the ball has carried, Bailey has been given out!

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith c †Buttler b Broad 19 (16b 2x4 1x6 25m) SR: 118.75

dismissalComment.html: and that's what he needs! Broad pitches up outside off, just a hint of movement away to take Smith's outside edge. Well bowled, just rolled his fingers across the ball to create some cut

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell c †Buttler b Stokes 26 (26b 2x4 0x6 39m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: strikes first ball! An excellent match continues for Stokes. It was a back-of-a-length cutter, gripped a little on the pitch, which Maxwell tried to swing with all his power through the leg side but only got a thin edge to Buttler

dismissalText.commentary: Dan Christian c Ballance b Broad 23 (19b 1x4 1x6 48m) SR: 121.05

dismissalComment.html: Christian is gone now, yet another batsman in this match caught at third man. He's swung hard and a thickish edge is taken by a sliding Gary Ballance

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: James Faulkner c †Buttler b Stokes 2 (11b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 18.18

dismissalComment.html: another wicket and it's the big one! Faulkner will not be the hero today. The extra bounce has done for Faulkner as it did for Maxwell. Faulkner backs off a touch and tries to slash through off and a top edge sails safely through to Buttler

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Johnson b Stokes 6 (8b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: bowled, middle stump! Johnson went the big swing and Stokes was accurate enough to hit. This is England's match now, it's hard to see any way out for Australia.
